               <p>MAJOR HAXBY sworn.</p>
               <p>William and 
               <persName id="t17760522-44-person554">
                  Richard
                   Sampson
               <interp inst="t17760522-44-person554" type="surname" value="Sampson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-44-person554" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-44-person554" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             are <rs id="t17760522-44-viclabel197" type="occupation">wholesale upholsterers</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760522-44-victim551 t17760522-44-viclabel197"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17760522-44-victim553 t17760522-44-viclabel197"></join>; I am a manager for them; on the 4th of April I packed up a parcel of moreen, and a gross of bed-lace, and directed it to 
               <persName id="t17760522-44-person555">
                  Edward
                   Goodyer
               <interp inst="t17760522-44-person555" type="surname" value="Goodyer"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-44-person555" type="given" value="Edward"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-44-person555" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , at Dover; it was delivered by our porter to the wharfiners at the keys, and the wharfage paid; about an hour after, the prisoner was detected with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17760522-44-person556">
                  ROBERT
                   SHIRLEY
               <interp inst="t17760522-44-person556" type="surname" value="SHIRLEY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17760522-44-person556" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
